The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, January 14, 2004  Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee today turned a fair organised by an arm of the government into an election roadshow, admitting that Muslims were under-represented in the public sector and announcing a slew of sops. ... | Mamata Banerjee today invited director Sandip Ray to film the lives of coal mine workers. ... | Once known for setting the tracks on fire, Sprint Queen P.T. Usha walked off the sports complex here today  possibly in tea ... | Police today recovered the decomposed body of a Class XII student from a field adjoining a spinning mill near Kalyani. ... | 					Focused: Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee sips tea at the minorities development corporation programme. Picture by Amit Datta
